 Ondo State Police command has said that it had deployed over 3,000 officers to various parts of the state to carry out special patrols on the highways till next month. The State Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO)  command, Femi Joseph, said this would prevent criminal activities, especially kidnapping on major highways in the state. Joseph, in a statement, said the police officers on patrol would monitor the troubled spot along Ikare-Owo road where the wife of a traditional ruler was recently kidnapped. According to him, the police officers would be on the road till the first of next month because of heavy flow of traffic on most of the roads in the state during the period. Joseph said the Commissioner of Police,  Adie Undie had held series of security meetings with top officers of the command on how to tackle kidnapping during and after the festive period. He expressed sadness over the resurgence of kidnapping of travelers on Owo-Ikare Akoko road and assured that the police would rescue those abducted on the highway last weekend. The PPRO noted that policemen would also be deployed to strategic locations in the state to forestall breakdown of law and order. His words “the Ondo State Police Command Once again reassures the people of the state of adequate security during this period. We also want to state that the kidnap incident that happened few days ago along Owo/Ikare road after a long period of peace and normalcy in that axis of the state is being tackled head-on by our officers who have been charged to not only rescue the victims unhurt, but also arrest the perpetrators of this wicked act. “People should not entertain any anxiety as we have increased our manpower deployment across the state and have also directed our intelligence department to improve their activities on crime prevention.’